@node "Intro" "Introduction"


@{b}Introduction@{ub}



Myzar is an MUI graphical front-end for the RC5-DES client. However, this is not
a simple GUI to start/stop the client, the way some other GUIs do with other CLI
programs (GMPlay, Mpega, PGP, archivers...), but a complex front-end with its
own features, which integrate and complete those made available by the
shell-only client. With the aid of this program using the RC5-DES client will be
as easy as with other platforms (namely: Win95 and Mac), for which native
GUI-only clients are available.

If you don't know what the RC5-DES contest is, have a look @{"here" link "rc5 challenge" 0}.


Myzar's main features are:


    * - Client output is displayed in an MUI listview

    * - The application can be iconified, no more windows around

    * - An alternative ("small") window, only displaying the information you
        are interested in.

    * - Two or more copies of Myzar can be started, useful to run two clients
        on PPC-equipped Amigas.

    * - Easy switch between different on-line modes (online, offline,
        runbuffers)

    * - Fetch & flush blocks with a mouse click

    * - Fetch & flush automatically when an Internet connection is detected

    * - Main client options configurable within the program

    * - Auto launch client, and auto iconify at startup

    * - Stats window: learn how well your client is doing over the time

    * - Arexx



But before trying the program, have a look at how to @{"configure" link "Config" 0} it.

People who already used version 1.1 may want to see what @{"changed" link "News" 0} since then.
@endnode

